				<navigationLabel>
					Food and Health
				</navigationLabel>
				<contentItems>
					<contentItem id="126">
						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							Beavers eat the inner layer of bark called the cambium.  They store big batches of sticks underwater, where they can access them all year round. Beavers even have lips behind their teeth, so they can bite and chew underwater, without getting a mouthful of water!
						</text>
