				<title>
					Danger Alert
				</title>
				<navigationLabel>
					Danger Alert
				</navigationLabel>
				<contentItems>
					<contentItem id="126">
						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							Wolves, coyotes, and lynx can catch a beaver when it is out of the water. But in the water, beavers are pretty safe. That's one of the main reasons that beavers build dams. The dams make a huge pond of water, that acts as a safety zone for the beavers. When danger is near, a beaver slaps his tail on the water to alert the other beavers.
						</text>
